# XFlickr — test factories and Faker

Canonical details: [`docs/04-development/testing.md`](../../docs/04-development/testing.md), skill [`testing-and-quality-gates`](../../ai/skills/testing-and-quality-gates/SKILL.md).

Rules:

- Every Eloquent model needs a factory (`HasFactory` + factory class)
- Incidental attributes: `Model::factory()`, `fake()`, `Tests\Support\FlickrNsid::fake()` — not hardcoded NSIDs/emails
- Assert from the created model (`$connection->connection_key`), never re-hardcode the same literal
- Flickr accounts: `CreatesFlickrConnection` (already Faker-backed)
- Crawler package models: `database/factories/Crawler/*`
- Hardcode only when the literal is the scenario (config admin email, forbidden production password)
